sourceINTEGERHow the participant came to the test based on HTTP referrer (the url the link the user clicked was on). 1=from front page of website that hosted the survey, 2=from google, 3=facebook, 4=any url containing ".edu" (so "xxx.edu" or "xxx.edu.au" etc., typically it appears these are students in a course where the professor linked the test in their course management software (e.g. moodle)), 5=wikipedia, 6=other source or empty source (empty source=not provided or direct traffic).
accuracyINTEGERAfter submission, subjects were instructed to indicate on a scale from 0000 the overall accuracy of their answers. Subjects were instructed to enter 0 if they did not want their data used. Only submissions with accuracy > 0 have been retained.
elapseINTEGERNumber of seconds between when the user started the test and when they submitted it .
ageINTEGERAge in years, only ages >= 13 retained.
genderINTEGER1 if "Male", 2 if "Female, 3 if "Other" (0 if missed).
